INSERT INTO `pgwp_posts` VALUES (1,4,'2012-07-15 13:35:25','2012-07-15 13:35:25','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn 2010 Paul Leinwand and Cesare Mainardi, two partners from Booz &amp; Co, proposed a simple question to corporate executives: Is your company disciplined enough to focus exclusively on what it does best? Their research discovered that most companies are not so disciplined, but those few that are enjoy \"sustainable, superior returns\" because of something they call \"the coherence premium.\"\r\n\r\nThe idea of coherence is simple enough: your strategy — the way you create value — leverages your unique capabilities to produce a highly differentiated product and service fit. The hard part: the coherent company focuses on what it does best in making every decision across every business. Obviously, that includes your <em>mobile strategy</em>.\r\n\r\nThat means, regardless of what business you are in, when it comes to developing your mobile strategy, don\'t start the way so many companies do <em>—</em> by baselining competitors, collecting favorites, or researching what leading companies have done. Instead look inside at your unique capabilities and the way you win. Maybe it\'s superior engineering, or breadth of product line, or vertical integration, or service after the sale... Whatever it is, that\'s the start your mobile strategy.\r\n\r\nNow you\'re ready to innovate on ways mobile can take the way you win, your unique capabilities, and your products and services and make them all more visible, more tangible, more accessible, more extensible, or simply, <strong>more</strong>.','Your business strategy is your mobile strategy','In 2010 Paul Leinwand and Cesare Mainardi, two partners from Booz & Co, proposed a simple question to corporate executives: Is your company disciplined enough to focus exclusively on what it does best? Their research discovered that most companies are not so disciplined, but those few that are enjoy \"sustainable, superior returns\" because of something they call \"the coherence premium.\"','publish','open','open','','your_business_strategy_is_your_mobile_strategy','','','2012-08-23 18:57:03','2012-08-23 18:57:03','',0,'http://70.87.136.174/~provingg/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2012-07-20 13:35:25','2012-07-20 13:35:25','<h1>Your business strategy made mobile</h1>\r\n<p class=\"pitch\">Mobile can transform your business, but it will take more than technology.\r\nLet Proving Ground show you how developing innovative tactics and technology that support your core business strategies can provide your company a sustainable competitive advantage.</p>','Home','','publish','open','closed','','home','','','2012-07-20 13:53:57','2012-07-20 13:53:57','',0,'http://70.87.136.174/~provingg/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(32,1,'2012-07-20 13:45:45','2012-07-20 13:45:45','<h1>Your business strategy made mobile</h1>\r\n<p class=\"pitch\">Mobile can transform your business, but it will take more than technology.\r\nLet Proving Ground show you how developing innovative tactics and technology that support your core business strategies can provide your company a sustainable competitive advantage.</p>','Home','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-3','','','2012-07-20 13:45:45','2012-07-20 13:45:45','',2,'http://70.87.136.174/~provingg/uncategorized/2-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(4,1,'2012-07-20 13:35:25','2012-07-20 13:35:25','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://70.87.136.174/~provingg/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision','','','2012-07-20 13:35:25','2012-07-20 13:35:25','',2,'http://70.87.136.174/~provingg/2012/07/20/2-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(5,1,'2012-07-20 13:36:36','2012-07-20 13:36:36','<h2>mobile strategy</h2>\r\nFor most companies, mobile is a strategic priority because of its ability to provide significant competitive advantage. Proving Ground uses its proven framework to help executive teams understand their opportunities, defining mobile objectives, and ideating specific short and long-term initiatives their achievement.\r\n<h2>Technology roadmap planning</h2>\r\nFor most companies, mobile is a strategic priority because of its ability to provide significant competitive advantage. Proving Ground uses its proven framework to help executive teams understand their opportunities, defining mobile objectives, and ideating specific short and long-term initiatives their achievement.\r\n<h2>Mobile application development Embedded device</h2>\r\nFor most companies, mobile is a strategic priority because of its ability to provide significant competitive advantage. Proving Ground uses its proven framework to help executive teams understand their opportunities, defining mobile objectives, and ideating specific short and long-term initiatives their achievement.\r\n<h2>software development</h2>\r\nFor most companies, mobile is a strategic priority because of its ability to provide significant competitive advantage. Proving Ground uses its proven framework to help executive teams understand their opportunities, defining mobile objectives, and ideating specific short a