ct concepts</li>\r\n	<li>Build and deploy the products</li>\r\n</ol>','Goal-based Strategy Framework','','inherit','open','open','','66-revision-8','','','2012-07-24 00:20:00','2012-07-24 00:20:00','',66,'http://www.provingground.net/66-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(80,3,'2012-07-23 22:31:12','2012-07-23 22:31:12','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn 2010 Paul Leinwand and Cesare Mainardi, two partners from Booz &amp; Co, proposed a simple question to corporate executives: Is your company disciplined enough to focus exclusively on what it does best? Their research discovered that most companies are not so disciplined, but those few that are enjoy \"sustainable, superior returns\" because of something they call \"the coherence premium.\"\r\n\r\nThe idea of coherence is simple enough: your strategy — the way you create value — leverages your unique capabilities to produce a highly differentiated product and service fit. The hard part: the coherent company focuses on what it does best in making every decision across every business. Obviously, that includes your <em>mobile strategy</em>.\r\n\r\nThat means, regardless of what business you are in, when it comes to developing your mobile strategy, don\'t start the way so many companies do <em>—</em> by baselining competitors, collecting favorites, or researching what leading companies have done. Instead look inside at your unique capabilities and the way you win. Maybe it\'s superior engineering, or breadth of product line, or vertical integration, or service after the sale... Whatever it is, that\'s the start your mobile strategy.\r\n\r\nNow you\'re ready to innovate on ways mobile can take the way you win, your unique capabilities, and your products and services and make them all more visible, more tangible, more accessible, more extensible, or simply, <strong>more</strong>.','Your business strategy is your mobile strategy','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-8','','','2012-07-23 22:31:12','2012-07-23 22:31:12','',1,'http://www.pr