ogy landscape, Danny co-founded Spun Logic in 1999, and steered it to become the largest interactive agency in Atlanta. Serving as CTO until its acquisition by Engauge in 2010, Danny set the tone for how it would successfully deliver for the best known brands in the southeast, including Home Depot, Dell, and Georgia-Pacific.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Travis Bailey</h2>\r\n<h3>Chief Technology Officer</h3>\r\nThe solutions we build today must be scalable, flexible and maintainable for years. As architect and hands-on developer on projects for Capital One, Southern Company and others, Travis has designed and lead the development of some serious data applications. His largest, a multi-million dollar trading platform, executes more than $11 billion in trades annually. At Proving Ground Travis defines the technologies and development techniques that best fit the needs of the solution and the capabilities of the client company.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Nick Webb</h2>\r\n<h3>Sr VP Innovation and Solutions Architect</h3>\r\nInnovation means building things that haven’t been built before. And while nearly anything is possible, some attempts at achieving them are nearly impossible. The common thread in Nick’s eclectic background is pushing the envelop — including pioneering the digital art program at the Atlanta College of Art, developing industry leading solutions at Air Defense, and solutioning the toughest DSL implementations for MindSpring during broadband’s infancy. Today Nick designs practicable technical solutions for Proving Ground’s most challenging technical problems.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Kyle Unverferth</h2>\r\n<h3>Big Systems Engineer</h3>\r\nSuccessful products get pounded, which is why Kyle constantly thinks in terms of scale. Adept at Scala, Ruby and most Java / C# frameworks, Kyle ensures that even massive transaction volumes don’t slow the user experience. Having once developed an MMO (massively multiplayer online) game for Mattel Corporation that supported 30,000 concurrent users on single server, Kyle now ensures PG client products can scale to their potential.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Jake Warhaftig</h2>\r\n<h3>Engagement Manager</h3>\r\nForward thinking concepts need pragmatic execution. Schooled in manufacturing design at RIT and credited with helping web-enable several of the businesses of Newell Rubbermaid, Jake decides what to build — and what not to build — in order to get maximum long-term value out of any development effort.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Rich Goidel</h2>\r\n<h3>Sr VP Operations</h3>\r\nDeveloping quality products requires quality processes. With a masters in production from the University of Miami and 30 years of experience getting diverse individuals to lend their best to complex productions and technical projects for over 200 companies — including Microsoft, UPS, GE and many others — Rich designs, implements and enforces end-to-end processes that enable Proving Ground to deliver on its promise.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Alan Deeter</h2>\r\n<h3>Strategy</h3>\r\nSound mobile strategies are built are solid business strategy. In his 20-year career, Alan has helped more than 60 companies and their divisions, Hewlett-Packard, McKesson, and SAP attain category leadership by creating new and different kinds of value for customers. Alan helps customers uncover mobile initiatives that create business value.','Who we are','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-8','','','2012-07-23 17:28:08','2012-07-23 17:28:08','',12,'http://www.provingground.net/12-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(85,3,'2012-09-04 11:03:35','2012-09-04 11:03:35','Proving Ground offices are located near historic Piedmont Park in mid Atlanta, Georgia.\n<div class=\"box clearfix\">\n<iframe style=\"float:left;margin-right:20px;\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=1440+Dutch+Valley+Pl+NE+Atlanta,+GA+30324&amp;aq