end, Proving Ground is a Gold Sponsor of the event and the sole sponsor of the all-important happy hour which concludes the day at 4:30 pm.\r\n\r\nEvent details:\r\n•    When: Saturday, August 18, 2011\r\n\r\n•    Where: GTRI Conference Center, 250 14th Street, NW, Atlanta, GA 30318\r\n\r\n•    Time: 9:00 am to 4:30 pm (Registration and networking begin at 8:30 am!)\r\n\r\n•    Cost: Free (plus attendees get lunch!)\r\n\r\n•    Happy Hour Afterwards!\r\n\r\nMore information on ProductCamp Atlanta can be found at <a title=\"ProductCamp Atlanta home page\" href=\"http://pcampatl.com\" target=\"_blank\">ProductCamp Atlanta.</a>','ProductCamp Atlanta 2012 convenes Saturday August 18 ','','inherit','open','open','','93-revision-6','','','2012-08-16 19:29:21','2012-08-16 19:29:21','',93,'http://www.provingground.net/93-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(137,3,'2012-07-24 11:39:49','2012-07-24 11:39:49','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAn increasing amount of the value delivered by business systems and applications — including enterprise applications — is through mobile. Today that value comes largely from mobile-enabling existing capabilities. Soon it will come from delivering entirely new capabilities resulting from mobile innovation.\r\n\r\nThe reason is that customers are driving mobile innovation today, and today\'s customer demands are modest. But as consumer applications grow more sophisticated, so will customer demands. BYOD (bring your own device) will become commonplace, and all workers — from the front line to the boardroom — will be mobile workers. That\'s when mobile will become a free-for-all of innovation driven by technology providers. Product category leadership will change hands, and entirely new product categories will be created.\r\n\r\nProving Ground helps established technology companies prepare, navigate, thrive the tumult by employing its framework for mobile evolution.  PG mobile evolution allows companies to plot a course from defense to market creation.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-74\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;\" title=\"goals-based_strategy_diagram\" src=\"http://www.provingground.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/goal-based_strategy_diagram.png\" alt=\"Goal-based Strategy Diagram\" width=\"394\" height=\"389\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>1. Objective = defense; Strategy = simple enablement</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>react to customer demand</li>\r\n	<li>achieve parity with competitors</li>\r\n	<li>protect maintenance revenues</li>\r\n	<li>enable some of the most common, most visible functions</li>\r\n	<li>for example, dashboards, look-ups, monitoring and alerting</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>2. Objective = incremental revenue; Strategy = complex enablement</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>satisfy customer demand</li>\r\n	<li>by leading the category in mobile functionality</li>\r\n	<li>generating incremental revenue satisfying customers who are highly mobile ready</li>\r\n	<li>enable many functions that translate to mobile devices</li>\r\n	<li>examples include transaction-oriented apps, data+communications apps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>3. Objective = differentiation; Strategy = simple innovation</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>deliver a discrete but fundamentally new capability</li>\r\n	<li>that anticipates customer demand rather than responding to it</li>\r\n	<li>enables a limited number of new or existing capabilities in an entirely new way</li>\r\n	<li>supports your core business strategy and creates visible differentiation</li>\r\n	<li>touches a limited number of systems and device types</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>4. Objective = market creation; Strategy = sophisticated innovation</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>create customer demand in a new, uncontested market space</li>\r\n	<li>offers entirely new customer capabilities or makes existing capabilities significantly faster, better, cheaper</li>\r\n	<li>leverages your company’s core capabilities but enables a new mobile-centric business strategy</li>\r\n	<li>may combine mobile applications with embedded systems, new and existing back-end applications</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis 4 part framework is delivered in a 5 step process. The scope of the process changes with the complexity of the framework part. But it’s completeness means you\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Understand your capabilities and current business strategy</li>\r\n	<li>Benchmark competitors, and assess users demands, needs and mobile maturity</li>\r\n	<li>Envision a mobile future and the solutions</li>\r\n	<li>Design, validate the product concepts</li>\r\n	<li>Build and deploy the products</li>\r\n</ol>','Goal-based Strategy Framework','','inherit','open','open','','66-revision-9','','','2012-07-24 11:39:49','2012-07-24 11:39:49','',66,'http://www.provingground.net/66-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(138,3,'2012-07-24 11:40:10','2012-07-24 11:40:10','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn 2010 Paul Leinwand and Cesare Mainardi, two partners from Booz &amp; Co, proposed a simple question to corporate executives: Is your company disciplined enough to focus exclusively on what it does best? Their research discovered that most companies are not so disciplined, but those few that are enjoy \"sustainable, superior returns\" because of something they call \"the coherence premium.\"\r\n\r\nThe idea of coherence is simple enough: your strategy — the way you create value — leverages your unique capabilities to produce a highly differentiated product and service fit. The hard part: the coherent company focuses on what it does best in making every decision across every business. Obviously, that includes your <em>mobile strategy</em>.\r\n\r\nThat means, regardless of what business you are in, when it comes to developing your mobile strategy, don\'t start the way so many companies do <em>—</em> by baselining competitors, collecting favorites, or researching what leading companies have done. Instead look inside at your unique capabilities and the way you win. Maybe it\'s superior engineering, or breadth of product line, or vertical integration, or service after the sale... Whatever it is, that\'s the start your mobile strategy.\r\n\r\nNow you\'re ready to innovate on ways mobile can take the way you win, your unique capabilities, and your products and services and make them all more visible, more tangible, more accessible, more extensible, or simply, <strong>more</strong>.','Your business strategy is your mobile strategy','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-9','','','2012-07-24 11:40:10','2012-07-24 11:40:10','',1,'http://www.provingground.net/1-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(142,3,'2012-08-27 20:06:09','2012-08-27 20:06:09','','.','linkedin','publish','open','open','','linkedin','','','2012-09-05 16:05:34','2012-09-05 16:05:34','',0,'http://www.provingground.net/?p=142',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(146,3,'2012-09-04 10:59:30','2012-09-04 10:59:30','Proving Ground offices are located on historic Peachtree Street in downtown Atlanta, Georgia.\r\n<div class=\"box clearfix\">\r\n<iframe style=\"float:left\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=1440+Dutch+Valley+Pl+NE+Atlanta,+GA+30324&amp;aq=&amp;sll=33.79326,-84.368849&amp;sspn=0.012108,0.022638&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=1440+Dutch+Valley+Pl+NE,+Atlanta,+Georgia+30324&amp;t=m&amp;ll=33.793272,-84.36882&amp;spn=0.021399,0.025749&amp;z=14&amp;iwloc=A&amp;output=embed\"></iframe><br /><small><a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=embed&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=1440+Dutch+Valley+Pl+NE+Atlanta,+GA+30324&amp;aq=&amp;sll=33.79326,-84.368849&amp;sspn=0.012108,0.022638&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=1440+Dutch+Valley+Pl+NE,+Atlanta,+Georgia+30324&amp;t=m&amp;ll=33.793272,-84.36882&amp;spn=0.021399,0.025749&amp;z=14&amp;iwloc=A\" style=\"color:#0000FF;text-align:left\">View Larger Map</a></small>\r\n<div class=\"address\">\r\n<h2>Address</h2>\r\n1440 Dutch Valley Pl NE\r\nSuite 250\r\nAtlanta, GA 3